# 🍾 Liquor Sales ETL Notebook
This notebook performs data loading, cleaning, transformation, and export for the Liquor Sales Analytics Project.

---

## 📥 1. Import Libraries

```python
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
```

---

## 📂 2. Load Raw CSV

```python
df = pd.read_csv("../data/liquor_sales.csv")
df.head()
```

---

## 🧹 3. Clean Column Names

```python
df.columns = df.columns.str.lower().str.replace(" ", "_")
df.columns
```

---

## 📅 4. Convert Date Column

```python
df["sale_date"] = pd.to_datetime(df["sale_date"], errors="coerce")
df["sale_date"].head()
```

---

## ❌ 5. Handle Missing Values

```python
df = df[df["sale_dollars"].notnull()]
df.isnull().sum()
```

---

## ➕ 6. Add Calculated Columns

```python
df["avg_bottle_price"] = df["sale_dollars"] / df["bottles_sold"]
df.head()
```

---

## 📊 7. Basic Exploratory Analysis

```python
df.describe()
```

---

## 🏙 8. City-Level Summary

```python
df.groupby("city")["sale_dollars"].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head()
```

---

## 🍾 9. Category Summary

```python
df.groupby("category")["sale_dollars"].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head()
```

---

## 📈 10. Monthly Trend

```python
df["month"] = df["sale_date"].dt.to_period("M")
df.groupby("month")["sale_dollars"].sum().head()
```

---

## 💾 11. Save Cleaned CSV

```python
df.to_csv("../data/liquor_sales_cleaned.csv", index=False)
print("Cleaned dataset saved successfully.")
```